Aneka Tambang, Chandra Asri, Medco: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-10-04T01:45:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/aneka-tambang-chandra-asri-medco-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 5.6 percent to 3,348.71.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures declined 1.5 percent to
$76.48 a barrel in after-hours trading in  New York , falling for
a third day.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, dropped 9.3 percent to 1,950 rupiah
and PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second-largest,
tumbled 11 percent to 117 rupiah.  Nickel producers: Nickel for three-month delivery jumped
8.1 percent to $19,025 a metric ton in  London  yesterday, the
steepest increase since Jan. 23, 2009. The metal last traded at
$18,500 a ton.  PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO IJ), the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, sank 7.4 percent to 2,800 rupiah
and PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ), the second-largest, retreated 6
percent to 1,410 rupiah.  PT Chandra Asri Petrochemical (TPIA IJ): The polypropylene
producer received a $465 million loan from seven local and
foreign banks, Bisnis  Indonesia  reported, citing Suryandi, the
Indonesian company’s corporate secretary. Chandra Asri plunged
11 percent to 3,250 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at  
 dboey@bloomberg.net  